PROCEDURE: Flexible bronchoscopy with cryo-resection, cautery snare and APC.
DETAILS: Vascular masses were id[REDACTED] occluding the LUL and LLL. The LUL lesion was resected via snare. The LLL lesion was extracted using a cryoprobe and ablated with APC. Hemostasis was secured. The LUL was recanalized; the LLL was partially cleared.
